  <refnamediv>
    <refname>comma</refname>
    <refpurpose> (,) column, instruction, argument separator</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      Commas are used to separate parameters in functions or 
      to separate entries of row  vectors.
    </para>
    <para>
      Blanks can also be used to separate entries in a row vector but
      use preferably commas.
    </para>
    <para>
      Also used to separate Scilab instructions.
      (Use <literal>;</literal> to have the result not displayed on the screen).
    </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[ 
a=[1,2,3;4,5,6];
a=1,b=1;c=2
 ]]></programlisting>
